headline: Supreme Court Tariff Shift Puts Nike Valuation And Margins Under Scrutiny
summary: U.S. Supreme Court ruling curbs presidential emergency tariff powers, affecting earlier duties on imports relevant to Nike. Administration quickly introduces new 15% global tariffs using different legal authority, keeping trade costs in flux for NYSE:NKE. Rapid policy reversal raises fresh questions around sourcing, pricing, and margin resilience for the footwear and apparel giant.
